input:
AITA for stretching in spandex shorts opposite a church | About once a week Judy runs speed intervals for training. There aren't any running tracks near Judy's house but about 1km away there is a quiet residential road which is flat, quiet, and almost exactly 400m long (the same length as a track). At the end of the road is a small local parish church. 

&#x200B;

When Judy is training intervals she usually jogs the 1km to the road to warm up, stops and does some dynamic stretching, and then starts her intervals (normally 400 or 800m long). In-between intervals Judy has short recovery sessions, where she'll sometimes jog slowly, walk, or stretch.

&#x200B;

The other day Judy was doing some stretching between reps on the bench at the end of the road, which is opposite the church. The weather recently has been fairly warm, but very grey and wet, so Judy was wearing a lightweight long-sleeve top to keep the worst of the rain off, and spandex running shorts (something like [this](https://www.nike.com/gb/t/fast-running-shorts-2c26G6)) because Judy figured she would be too hot in leggings. An older woman came up to Judy and told Judy that Judy was being very disrespectful for lingering and stretching in such small shorts outside a church, especially as there were also a lot of primary schools in the area. Judy apologised and moved onto another street to finish her intervals and stretching, but it wasn't really an ideal place to do speed sets because it's a lot busier and Judy often ends up having to stop for cars during the intervals. 

&#x200B;

So was Judy being disrespectful? Judy wasn't raised Christian and Judy doesn't want to upset people who are if what Judy was doing really was offensive. Judy would never do it on a Sunday morning when people are going into/coming out of a service, but this was around 3pm on a Monday afternoon and it seemed to be closed. Also as a Jew, Judy would feel perfectly comfortable doing the same outside a synagogue as long as it wasn't on a Saturday morning/holiday. Judy also wasn't deliberately trying to appear provocative at all, Judy was just doing some calf stretches ([like this](https://cdn1.medicalnewstoday.com/content/images/articles/322/322809/calf-wall-stretch.jpg)) because Judy's calf/achilles were giving Judy a bit of bother.

&#x200B;

If Judy is the asshole she'll try and find another place for the summer, because it's going to be too hot to wear leggings most of the time. But if she was just overreacting please let Judy know because it really is the best place anywhere nearby to practice speed (everywhere else is hilly or has too much traffic) and Judy will keep going.
